pull_request.body:
Created by `brew bump` --- Created with `brew bump-formula-pr`.
release notes 
## Release Notes

This release focuses on improving collection history management. The `slumber collections` subcommand is fairly niche, but is now a bit more powerful and user friendly.

### Added

- Add `slumber collections delete` subcommand to remove collections from history
- Add `slumber history rm` as an alias for `slumber history delete`
- Add filter box to collection select dialog. Less scrolling, more typing!

### Changed

- `slumber collections migrate` now accepts collection IDs in addition to paths
- `slumber collections list` now includes an ID column in its output

### Fixed

- Shell completion for the global `--file`/`-f` flag will now only `.yml`/`.yaml` files
- `slumber collections migrate` now accepts paths for files that don't exist on disk (as long as they existed as collections at some point)



## Install slumber 3.4.0

### Install prebuilt binaries via shell script

```sh
curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -LsSf https://github.com/LucasPickering/slumber/releases/download/v3.4.0/slumber-installer.sh | sh
```

### Install prebuilt binaries via powershell script

```sh
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -c "irm https://github.com/LucasPickering/slumber/releases/download/v3.4.0/slumber-installer.ps1 | iex"
```

### Install prebuilt binaries via Homebrew

```sh
brew install LucasPickering/tap/slumber
```

issue.title: feat: service post install/uninstall events and php extensions improvements
issue.body:
I created a plugin to fetch/allow to install extra PHP extensions and I was looking for a reliable way to now when a service got installed and do something. **I setup a template method pattern to adhere to the install Interface and ensure the event is always triggered during install without having to call `parent::install()`** I think other services also would have this benefit allowing other plugins developers to hook those methods to perform some actions during service installations.

I also modified slightly the `extensions.tsx` to make it extendable and allow it to receive `type_data` information this way we can extend the functionality of the current drop down instead of creating another one somewhere else.

Also php extensions install rules where kinda hardcoded, reading the `config` values I think it's better to open that for some extensibility.

This changes won't impact existing functionality but it will open interesting possibilities like this: https://github.com/arzola/extra-php-extensions

commits.message:
Allow building payjoin crate with no default features

Previously, the payjoin crate would fail to build if none of the
features 'v1', 'v2', or 'directory' were enabled, due to an explicit
compile_error! macro. This prevented the use of tools like
cargo-all-features for comprehensive CI and dead code detection.

This change removes the compile_error! and replaces it with a
doc-only module that is included when no features are enabled,
making the crate a no-op in that configuration. The documentation
and Cargo.toml are updated to clarify that at least one of the
main features must be enabled for any functionality.

This enables better CI, linting, and future modularity, while
preserving clear guidance for users and contributors.

Closes #921

pull_request.title: feat: implement comprehensive log view for tview UI mode
pull_request.body:
## Summary
- Implemented a fully-featured log view for the tview-based TUI mode
- Added streaming log support with search, filter, and various display options
- Integrated log view navigation from container list views

## Features

### Core Functionality
- **Log Streaming**: Real-time log streaming from Docker containers with context cancellation
- **Search**: Regex-based search with highlighting and navigation (n/N for next/previous)
- **Filter**: Filter logs to show only matching lines
- **Buffer Management**: Automatic buffer limiting to 10,000 lines for memory efficiency

### Display Options
- **Auto-scroll**: Automatically scroll to new log entries
- **Line Wrap**: Toggle text wrapping
- **Timestamps**: Show/hide Docker timestamps
- **Line Numbers**: Display line numbers during search

### Keyboard Shortcuts
- `l` - View logs (from container list views)
- `j/k` - Scroll down/up
- `g/G` - Go to top/bottom
- `PgUp/PgDn` - Page up/down
- `/` - Search
- `f` - Filter
- `n/N` - Next/previous search result
- `w` - Toggle wrap
- `t` - Toggle timestamps
- `a` - Toggle auto-scroll
- `p` - Pause/resume streaming
- `c` - Clear logs
- `r` - Refresh logs
- `Esc` - Clear search/filter

### Implementation Details
- Added `ExecuteStreamingCommand` to `internal/docker/executor.go` for streaming support
- Created comprehensive `LogView` in `internal/tui/views/log_view.go`
- Integrated with `DockerContainerListView` and `ComposeProcessListView`
- Added callback mechanism for view switching
- Thread-safe implementation with proper mutex protection

## Testing
- Created comprehensive test suite in `log_view_test.go`
- All tests passing
- Code formatted and linted

## Test Plan
- [x] Log streaming works for running containers
- [x] Search functionality finds and highlights matches
- [x] Filter correctly shows only matching lines
- [x] Navigation keys work as expected
- [x] Buffer limit prevents memory issues
- [x] Integration with container list views works
- [x] All unit tests pass

pull_request.title: Add FantasyPros projection source with functional architecture
pull_request.body:
This PR implements a new projection source class for FantasyPros that follows the established functional architecture pattern used by other sources like ESPN and ETR.

## Implementation Details

The implementation consists of three main components:

**FantasyProsFetcher** - Handles HTTP requests and URL building for FantasyPros projections:
- Supports all positions: QB, RB, WR, TE, K, DST
- Handles different scoring formats: PPR, Half-PPR, Standard
- Supports weekly and season-long projections (draft, 1-17, custom weeks)
- Generates proper URLs like `https://www.fantasypros.com/nfl/projections/qb.php?week=draft`

**FantasyProsParser** - Parses FantasyPros HTML table structure:
- Handles different table layouts for QB vs skill positions
- Resolves duplicate column names in QB tables (ATT/YDS/TDS appear twice for passing/rushing)
- Extracts player names, teams, positions, and all fantasy statistics
- Differentiates between passing stats (`pass_att`, `pass_yds`) and rushing stats (`rush_att`, `rush_yds`)

**FantasyProsProjections** - Main orchestrator class:
- Coordinates fetcher, parser, and standardizer components
- Provides unified API following established patterns
- Includes comprehensive column mapping for all FantasyPros statistics

## Usage Example

```python
from nflprojections import FantasyProsProjections

# Season-long QB projections
fp = FantasyProsProjections(position="qb", scoring="ppr", week="draft")
projections = fp.fetch_projections()

# Weekly RB projections with Half-PPR scoring
fp = FantasyProsProjections(position="rb", scoring="half", week=8)
projections = fp.fetch_projections()
```

## Technical Highlights

- **Smart Column Mapping**: Handles QB tables with duplicate column names by prefixing with `pass_` or `rush_`
- **Flexible URL Generation**: Automatically includes scoring parameters only when needed (non-QB positions, non-draft weeks)
- **Robust HTML Parsing**: Extracts player information from complex FantasyPros table structure
- **Complete Test Coverage**: 13 unit tests covering all components and integration scenarios
- **Consistent Architecture**: Follows the same functional component pattern as existing sources

The implementation supports all the sample URLs mentioned in the issue:
- `https://www.fantasypros.com/nfl/projections/qb.php?week=draft`
- `https://www.fantasypros.com/nfl/projections/rb.php?week=draft&scoring=PPR`
- `https://www.fantasypros.com/nfl/projections/wr.php?week=1&scoring=HALF`

Fixes #58.
